## Order API

This API is used for order data postback. Once the purchase is done and API get called, ShopBack will receive the data and keep it in system for further validation.

### HTTP Request Of Order API

`GET http://shopback.go2cloud.org/aff_lsr`

| Parameter | Description | Necessary | Type |
| --------- | ----------- | :-------: | ------- |
| offer_id | Order API ID in ShopBack. | Y | String |
| amount | Amount of the order has been made in NTD. | Y | Float |
| adv_sub | Order ID of the order has been made. | Y | String |
| adv_sub2 | String that refer to specific tier set in ShopBack.(define by merchant) | N | String |
| adv_sub3 | SKU of the order has been made | N | String |
| adv_sub4 | conversion_unique_id | N | String |
| adv_sub5 |  | N |  |
| security_token |  | Y | String |
| transaction_id | Hash value for ShopBack to identify each user and give cashback</br>(default to expire after postback) | Y | String |

